# Flotta — LOCAL dev settings.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      # .env is gitignored; never commit real values
#
# Loaded automatically by the justfile (`set dotenv-load := true`), so every
# `just` recipe sees these. Note that `just` loads a file named exactly `.env`
# — a `.env.local` is NOT read.
#
# Two groups below: settings that configure YOUR MACHINE, and provider
# credentials that are forwarded into the worker container as a Modal Secret.

# --- Modal target ----------------------------------------------------------

# Which Modal profile (= workspace) every modal recipe uses. Pinned explicitly
# so a `modal profile activate` for some other project can never redirect a
# Flotta build into the wrong workspace.
#
# Create the profile (switch to the Flotta workspace in the Modal dashboard
# first — the token is minted for whatever workspace that browser session is
# in), then verify with `just modal-whoami`:
#
#   modal token new --profile flotta --no-activate
#
FLOTTA_MODAL_PROFILE=flotta

# Optional: pin a non-default Modal *environment* within that workspace.
# Modal reads this variable natively — leave it unset to use the workspace
# default, which is right for v0.1.
#MODAL_ENVIRONMENT=main

# --- Provider credentials (forwarded to the worker) ------------------------
#
# These three ARE read by the worker, but indirectly: `provision.py` collects
# whichever of them are set locally and ships them to the container as a Modal
# Secret (`Secret.from_local_environ`), so the key never travels as a plain
# function argument. Leave them unset and the worker still boots — it reports
# "missing provider config" instead, which is exactly what the $0 `dry_run`
# lifecycle path relies on.
#
# !! The secret is snapshotted at `modal deploy` time, NOT per call. After
# !! changing any value here you MUST re-run `just deploy`, or the deployed
# !! function keeps serving the old (or empty) secret.
#
# Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint works. Hermes's own default is OpenRouter;
# swap the base URL and model for OpenAI, Nous Portal, a local vLLM, etc.
#
# Needed only for `just e2e-live` and non-dry-run spawns.
#
#FLOTTA_MODEL=anthropic/claude-sonnet-4
#FLOTTA_MODEL_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
#FLOTTA_API_KEY=sk-or-...

# OPENAI_BASE_URL / OPENAI_API_KEY are honoured as fallbacks for the two above,
# so an existing OpenAI-style environment works without renaming anything.

# --- Worker runtime (NOT set here) -----------------------------------------
#
# The remaining worker variables are per-spawn, not per-machine: the spawner
# passes them into each container, so setting them here has no effect.
#
#   FLOTTA_TASK        the task prompt          (set by spawn_worker)
#   FLOTTA_TIMEOUT_S   hard task timeout, 900s  (spawn_worker's timeout_s)
#   FLOTTA_ONESHOT     run-once vs. serve mode
#   FLOTTA_HOST/PORT   MCP bind address         (never 3000 — reserved)
#   FLOTTA_AUTH_TOKEN  bearer token for the worker's MCP endpoint
#   FLOTTA_TOOLSETS    CSV of Hermes toolsets   (unset = Hermes default)
#   HERMES_HOME        ephemeral Hermes store, /tmp/hermes
#
# The authoritative table is the module docstring of:
#
#   src/flotta/worker/config.py
